1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 15.1-02 and a new section to
2 chapter 54-44.4 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to duties of the superintendent of
3 public instruction and the establishment of a government spending database; to provide an
4 appropriation; and to provide an effective date.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 15.1-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Training of school officials.
9 The superintendent of public instruction shall:
10 1. Contract for training servicesfor school board members, superintendents, principals,
11 and business managers relating to the requirements of section 2 of this Act .
12 2. Ensure the training includes academic best practices, personnel management,
13 financial operations, facility planning, and regulatory compliance.
14 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 54-44.4 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
15 and enacted as follows:
16 Government spending database - Requirements - State treasurer - Office of
17 management and budget - Superintendent of public instruction.
18 1. As used in this section, "submitting party" means:
19 a. A budget unit under section 54 - 44.1 - 04 ;
20 b. A political subdivision;
21 c. A school district; and
22 d. An institution under the control of the state board of higher education.
23 2. The state treasurer shall collect data from submitting parties and establish and
24 maintain a government spending database that is accessible without cost through the
