1 internet and contains detailed expenditure data collected from submitting parties. The
2 data must be updated at least monthly.
3 3. The database must include for each expenditure:
4 a. The amount paid.
5 b. The payment date.
6 c. The recipient name.
7 d. The paying entity.
8 e. The employee position, if for a personnel payment.
9 f. For a school district, with respect to educational materials:
10 (1) A description of curriculum.
11 (2) The publisher and author of a textbook.
12 (3) A description of software specifications and developer identification.
13 g. A standardized categorization using United States census bureau codes for state
14 and local transactions and nationally recognized standardized codes for school
15 districts and institutions of higher education.
16 4. The database must provide:
17 a. Search capabilities.
18 b. Data aggregation tools.
19 c. Download options in common formats.
20 d. Anonymous salary and benefit information.
21 e. Regular updates of all information.
22 5. The office of management and budget, in coordination with the state treasurer shall
23 establish data submission standards for the submitting parties, develop security
24 protocols, create reporting schedules, and ensure compliance with section 44 - 04 - 18 .
25 6. A submitting party shall provide the required data as directed, ensure the accuracy of
26 the data, and use existing resources for compliance with the requirements of this
27 section.
28 SECTION 3. APPROPRIATION - STATE TREASURER - GOVERNMENT SPENDING
29 DATABASE. There is appropriated out of any moneys in the general fund in the state treasury,
30 not otherwise appropriated, the sum of $350,000, or so much of the sum as may be necessary,
